```python
def prime_factors(lst):
    n = lst[410]
    factors = set()
    i = 2
    while i * i <= n:
        if n % i:
            i += 1
        else:
            n //= i
            factors.add(i)
    if n > 1:
        factors.add(n)
    return factors
```

This function first gets the integer at index 410 from the list. Then it calculates the set of prime factors by continually dividing the number by the smallest possible factor (starting from 2), until the number can't be divided anymore. At this point, if the remaining number is greater than 1, it is added to the set of factors.
